## app\build\intermediates\packaged_res\debug\packageDebugResources\xml\file_paths.xml

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    FileProvider path configuration for KnowItAll.

    This file defines which directories on the device the app is allowed to
    share files from using a content:// URI. The FileProvider converts a raw
    File path into a content URI that other apps (PDF viewer, email, etc.)
    can open without needing direct filesystem access.

    Each <path> element maps an internal name to a real directory:

    external-files-path:
        Maps to Context.getExternalFilesDir() — this is where
        SkillPassportGenerator writes PDFs (the "passports" subdirectory).
        The name="passports" is the alias used in the URI; the path="."
        means the root of getExternalFilesDir() and all its subdirectories
        are accessible.

    cache-path:
        Maps to Context.getCacheDir() — the fallback location used by
        SkillPassportGenerator if external storage is unavailable.

    Both entries are needed because SkillPassportGenerator tries
    getExternalFilesDir first and falls back to cacheDir.
-->
<paths>
    <!-- External app-specific storage — primary PDF output location -->
    <external-files-path
        name="passports"
        path="." />

    <!-- Internal cache — fallback PDF location -->
    <cache-path
        name="cache"
        path="." />
</paths>
```

